  "id": "75927d22-7232-568d-aded-756e16ad4983",
  "slug": "crock-pot-pork-adobo",
  "name": "Crock Pot Pork Adobo",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "Crock Pot Pork Adobo or Slow Cooked Pork Adobo is the most tender adobo dish that I\u2019ve ever had. Imagine slow cooking pork adobo for 5 hours or more \u2014 It\u2019s tasty, super tender, and worth the wait. I could not ask for more, but then I had hard boiled eggs to go with it. I feel like the luckiest man on earth (wink).",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Combine the pork shoulder, soy sauce, garlic, bay leaves, sugar, oyster sauce, and whole peppercorn in a bowl. Mix well. Let it stay for at least 30 minutes so that the pork can absorb the flavors."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Transfer the content of the bowl to a slow cooker or crock pot. Pour-in the beef broth. Set the level to high, cover, and slow cook for 5 hours."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Add the vinegar and salt. Continue to slow cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Add the boiled eggs. Transfer to a serving bowl."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Serve. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 8,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 6,
  "preparation_time_minutes": 30,
